data.name: Classic Macaroni and Cheese
data.quickTastyDescription: Creamy, cheesy, and totally comforting, this classic dish is a family favorite!
detailedCookingInstructions: Boil a large pot of salted water and cook the elbow macaroni according to package instructions until al dente. Drain and set aside.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt the butter. Stir in the flour and cook for about 1 minute to create a roux.
Gradually whisk in the milk, ensuring there are no lumps. Continue to cook, stirring frequently, until the mixture thickens.
Once thickened, reduce heat to low and stir in the cheddar cheese until melted and smooth.
Combine the cooked macaroni with the cheese sauce, mixing well to coat all the pasta.
Season with salt, black pepper, and paprika to taste. Serve hot.
